In the black and white photo, which was taken by Josh Shinner, the children are seen sitting on a wooden bench.

Shinner also took the image used on the family's Christmas card this year.

The couple posted the picture on social media, writing "Wishing everyone a very Merry Christmas, from our family to yours! W & C".

In their Christmas card image, released earlier this month, the family was seen together in another black and white photo arranged around Princess Charlotte sitting on a chair.

They were all wearing white shirts, with Catherine, Princess of Wales, and daughter Charlotte, eight, wearing jeans, while the Prince of Wales wore black trousers along with son Prince George, 10, and Prince Louis, five, who was in shorts.

In the picture the couple shared on Christmas Day, the three children seem to be wearing the same clothes and shoes as in the Christmas card image.

The family is at Sandringham in Norfolk for Christmas Day and is attending a church service in the morning.

Catherine hosted the Together At Christmas carol service event at Westminster Abbey, which was broadcast on Christmas Eve.

Once upon a time, there was a beautiful princess who lived in a castle surrounded by a vast and lush forest. The forest was home to all sorts of creatures, including a wise and ancient tree known as the Tree of Knowledge.

The princess was curious and adventurous, and she often ventured into the forest to explore its wonders. One day, while wandering through the trees, she came upon the Tree of Knowledge. The tree spoke to her, telling her that it held the secrets of the universe and that she could learn all she needed to know by listening to its whispers.

The princess was fascinated and spent many days sitting beneath the tree, listening to its wisdom. As she did so, she began to understand the secrets of the universe and gained a deep understanding of the world around her.

But as time went on, the princess grew restless. She wanted to share her newfound knowledge with the world, but she knew that the Tree of Knowledge was a secret that she must keep to herself. So she decided to embark on a journey to find a way to share the secrets of the universe without revealing the location of the Tree of Knowledge.

She traveled far and wide, meeting all sorts of people and learning about the different cultures and traditions of the world. Along the way, she discovered that the Tree of Knowledge was not the only source of wisdom and that there were many other ways to learn and grow.

Finally, after many years of traveling and searching, the princess returned to her castle. She had learned much on her journey and had found a way to share the secrets of the universe with the world. She wrote a book detailing all that she had learned, and it quickly became a bestseller.

But the princess was not content to rest on her laurels. She continued to seek out new knowledge and to share it with the world. And as she did so, she realized that the Tree of Knowledge was not just a source of wisdom, but a symbol of the endless possibilities that lay before her.

In a world where knowledge is power, the Tree of Knowledge was the source of all wisdom. It was a tall, majestic tree with branches that reached towards the sky. The leaves were green and shimmered in the sunlight, and the trunk was as strong as steel.

The Tree of Knowledge was guarded by a group of ancient guardians who protected it with their lives. They were known as the Keepers of the Tree, and their job was to ensure that the Tree of Knowledge remained safe and protected.

But one day, a young man named Ethan stumbled upon the Tree of Knowledge while he was out exploring the forest. He was amazed by its beauty and felt a deep connection to it.

Ethan knew that he had to protect the Tree of Knowledge, so he decided to become a Keeper of the Tree. He trained hard and learned all he could about the Tree of Knowledge. He learned how to care for it and how to protect it from harm.

As Ethan grew older, he became the leader of the Keepers of the Tree. He was a wise and knowledgeable man who was respected by all.

But one day, a group of evil men discovered the Tree of Knowledge and wanted to use its power for their own gain. They attacked the Keepers of the Tree and tried to take the Tree of Knowledge for themselves.

Ethan and the Keepers of the Tree fought bravely, but they were outnumbered and outmatched. Ethan knew that he had to do something to protect the Tree of Knowledge.

So Ethan came up with a plan. He used his knowledge of the Tree of Knowledge to create a magical spell that would protect the Tree from harm. He cast the spell, and the Tree of Knowledge was protected from harm.

Ethan and the Keepers of the Tree were victorious, and the Tree of Knowledge was safe. Ethan had used his knowledge to protect the Tree of Knowledge and ensure that its power would be used for good.

Ethan was hailed as a hero, and the Tree of Knowledge continued to be a source of wisdom and knowledge for generations to come.
